<subSubSection lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="40" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="10.[140,1108,1398,1672]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,335,1539,1565]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[185,330,1539,1565]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" reason="1">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
As for male of 
<taxonomicName box="[501,624,1539,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acontia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="areloides">
<emphasis box="[501,518,1540,1566]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[532,624,1539,1565]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">areloides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
excepting the dorsal hindwing, which in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dyar" authorityYear="1907" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Acontia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="areletta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">A. areletta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is pure white, without a fuscous marginal band. Th e female is unknown. 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[260,345,1610,1636]" captionStart="Figures 20-22" captionStartId="8.[140,222,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[160,1052,173,1547]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[140,1108,162,1594]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="Figures 20-22. Acontia areli group male genitalia (left – ventral; right – lateral). 20 A. geminocula, 21 A. albifusa, 22 A. areletta." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3810557" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3810557/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
; 2 dissections) 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[522,537,1610,1636]" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">–</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[546,607,1611,1636]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">uncus</emphasis>
: decurved, very long and narrow with very slightly expanded rounded apex. 
<taxonomicName box="[526,610,1646,1671]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Manica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="37" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[526,610,1646,1671]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="37">Manica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(memranous tube posterior to juxta) with
</paragraph>
